description: In a far flung dystopian society, where mankind and machine-kind coexist in an uneasy alliance overseen by a shadowy government, one man is reborn with the power to heal a people‚Ä¶ot destroy it. His name is Orlak. He awoke one day with no memory of his past and no plans for his future. His hands have been replaced with flesh ripping steel and when he sleeps, he finds them covered with blood. He is, in his own words, a puzzle with ten missing pieces.

description:
In the burning flames of an ancient city, Death discovers his first clue on the hunt for a rogue demon. As he travels further into the depths of the plague-ridden city, he calls to the souls of the dead . . . and confronts the one who would harm the Kingdom of Man!

Death comes to Earth in 1722, finding Marseilles utterly devastated. After finding a clue, he finally faces the demon he came to slay - but it's not a demon, but one of Abaddon's own angels.
name: Death's Door, part 3
